HEADWORD: Falcade
<hw>Fal*cade"</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧l*k⟦amac⟧d")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.,
ultimately fr. L. <ets>falx</ets>, <ets>falcis</ets>, a sickle or
scythe.]</ety> <fld>(Man.)</fld> <def>The action of a horse, when he
throws himself on his haunches two or three times, bending himself, as
it were, in very quick curvets.</def> <rj><au>Harris.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

